dismissalText.commentary: Peter Chase lbw b Rance 1 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50

commentTextItems.html: that's it its all over. Chase gets hit plumb in front of the stumps. New Zealand win by 51 runs.

commentPostTextItems.html: What an exciting match that was today. Niall O'Brien battled hard scored a fantastic maiden ODI century.
Yet again though it was Spin bowling that Ireland couldn't cope with. Santner ending up with his best ever figures and a five for.
With the win today, New Zealand get four points and move to the top of the tri-series table.
The presentations have just finished and Mitchell Santner has been named man of the match for his five for.
So that just leaves me to thank you for following my commentary today, hopefully you will join me on Wednesday when New Zealand will be taking on Bangladesh at Clontarf.
Until then this is Justin Smyth saying goodnight from a sunny Malahide. Goodnight!

commentTextItems.html: comes round the wicket to the left-handed Murtagh. Hits the ball up to long-on
Chase lifts the ball over the top of mid-wicket to get off the mark
the batsmen crossed so Murtagh is on strike. Hits the lasy ball of the over back to Santner. Ends up his allocation with a five for

clipped the ball down to long leg, shout is two but its not on. The fielder gets the ball back in quickly and so O'Brien is still not on strike.

commentTextItems.html: good ball from Rance, inswinging and McCarthy can only get in line and defend the ball back to the bowler
O'Brien looks to hit over the top again, its wide of off-stump so its sliced out to the cover sweeper
clipped through square leg and that's another run chalked off
driven through the covers, a mis-field on the rope means they get a second
dropped by Worker, O'Brien hits the ball to long-on. Worker gets under the ball and just can't hold on. Could be an expensive drop that
defends into the off-side and McCarthy wants the run, O'Brien wants the strike and so sends him back.

dismissalText.commentary: William Porterfield c Latham b Kuggeleijn 12 (16b 2x4 0x6) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: its wide of off-stump and Porterfield reaches out for the ball. Takes the outside edge and Latham takes a good catch diving to his right at second slip. Wicket maiden to boot.

headshotImage.caption: Scott Kuggeleijn player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Paul Stirling b Kuggeleijn 14 (14b 1x4 1x6) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: The Stumps go flying! Stirling was trying to play positively, looks to drive the ball and a little inswing does for him. Off and Middle stump gets taken out of the ground.

headshotImage.caption: Mitchell Santner player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mitchell Santner player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Niall O'Brien st †Ronchi b Santner 109 (131b 9x4 5x6) SR: 83.2

dismissalComment.html: that could well be it for Ireland's hopes. O'Brien decides to charge down the pitch to Santner, the ball spins past the bat and its another easy stumping for the keeper. What an innings from O'Brien though.

dismissalText.commentary: Andy Balbirnie c & b Santner 36 (50b 5x4 0x6) SR: 72

dismissalComment.html: what a way to get out! Balbirnie sweeps the ball, doesn't quite time it. Goes up and hits his helmet, Santner dives forward and takes the catch. What an unlucky way to get out.

headshotImage.caption: Ish Sodhi player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kevin O'Brien lbw b Sodhi 1 (3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: Well it didn't work. O'Brien goes back in the crease, to a ball he should have gone forward to. Gets hit on the pads in front of the stumps. No doubt about that one, he is a gonna.

Ross Taylor has scored 51 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for NZ breaking Nathan Astle's record
